    Following is the class structure of the Node class:

    class Node {
        int data;
        Node next;

        Node(int data) {
            this.data = data;
            this.next = null;
        }
    }

***************************************************************/

public class Solution {
	public static Node getListAfterAddingNodes(Node head, int k) {

        Node curr = head;
        while(curr != null){
            int sum  = 0;
            int cnt = 0;
            Node temp = curr;


            while(temp != null && cnt < k){
                sum += temp.data;
                temp = temp.next;
                cnt++;
            }

            Node nextNode = new Node(sum);
            Node kthNode = getKthNode(curr,k);

            if(kthNode != null){
                nextNode.next = kthNode.next;
                kthNode.next = nextNode;
                curr = nextNode.next;
            }else{
                temp = curr;
                while(temp.next != null){
                    temp = temp.next;
                }
                temp.next = nextNode;
                break;
            }
        }


;
        return head;

        
    }

    public static Node getKthNode(Node head,int k){

        int cnt = 0;
        Node temp = head;
        while(temp != null && cnt < k-1){
            temp = temp.next;
            cnt++;
        }
        return temp;

    }
}

You are given a Singly Linked List of integers and an integer 'K'.

Your task is to modify the linked list by inserting a new node after every 'K' node in the linked list with the node value being equal to the sum of the previous 'K' nodes.
Note :
If you reach a situation when the number of nodes remaining in the linked list is less than 'K' but greater than zero, just insert a node with the value equal to the sum of the remaining nodes.


eg :- 1 2 3 4 5 6 7  k = 3
